8562,7/A material catalyst unrewarded with expected price action is as close to a clear GTFO signal as the market gods will ever give

8564,5/Positioning - not fundamentals - matters most as a boundary condition at market extremes
8565,4/Differentiation always monetizes best when in the future tense; it is very hard to get paid on a differentiated view of present conditions

8569,"The past 2 years around this time, I‚Äôve tweeted out some ‚Äúlessons learned and re-learned‚Äù from the year just ended; thought I‚Äôd do it again:"

8571,"And with that, good luck to all in the year ahead."
8572,"Looking at companies at enterprise/not equity level is perpetual source of edge, but never more so than when credit cycle begins to sputter"
8573,"It always pays to be the person IR is sick of hearing from; the more frequent the conversations, the easier to appraise changes in tone"
8574,Thematic investing is particularly in tune with bull mkts but is playground of least informed shareholders‚Ä¶expect extreme vol as mkt turns
8575,Mgmt perpetually overconfident in ability to pass on cost inflation; career/comp risk for sales teams typically pulls in opposite direction
8576,Ignoring macro drivers no better than ignoring basic industry competitive dynamics..in fact worse bc mgmt at least has clue about the latter
8577,Catalyst-driven investing works well for stocks w/natural shareholder base but poor return on volatility when catalyst is only reason to own
8578,Later stages of any bull mkt are increasingly flow &amp; positioning driven; coherent view on who incremental buyer of any security is is a must
8579,"Multiple a biz is afforded is a direct derivative of mgmt credibility; even w/ biz that can ""run itself"" to own is to invite unforced error"
8580,Return on one's time is as important as return on an investment; some of best stocks can be suboptimal investments bc of time they consume
8581,Some lessons learned and re-learned in '15 that I figured I'd share as the calendar turns...
8582,(10) Mkts fear containable (ie non-airborne) diseases far more than they fear potentially uncontainable govts that are threatened w/collapse
8583,(9) corporate boards are not unlike investors -- their behavior gets shaped largely by actions of peers -- and so sector m&amp;a can cascade
8584,(8) activists are often more about choosing targets that protect/promote their franchise than those w/real room for impact...follower beware
8585,"(7) an investment thesis that begins and ends with ""buybacks"" in an industry that is structurally changing is not a thesis"
8586,(6) the pt at which investors embrace/re-rate tax structures is the pt at which the assets employing these structures test mkt's generosity
8587,"(5) when core/entrenched mkt paradigms shift (ie oil prices), being late to the equity/credit wreckage is far preferable to being early"
8588,(4) allocators can create traffic jams: floods of capital into sector-specific funds (TMT) nets ST outperformance but indigestion thereafter
8589,(3 cont'd) ....valuations and corporate decisions (ie spinning off complete crap)
8590,(3) basic investing playbooks (buy the spin!) increasingly fail to work when herd behavior creates feedback loop into starting point...
8591,"(2) Biz have hidden exposure to many things(fx, end mkts) - these variables are so impactful when important precisely bc they are so ignored"
8592,"(1) bull mkts create bull mkts in relative valuation investing, where asset quality can become a secondary detail to industry SIC code"
